      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CONTRADICTION (1) failed to come into contention last start after losing his position early at Healesville, but prior to that won by 1.5 lengths at Healesville (19.24) beating Mums Pearl in a Grade 5 H on June 7. Form from his last run is proving to be solid. Can make amends. PAPA EASY (2) ran below best last time finishing seventh (26.35) over 460m at Geelong from Box 3. Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Likely to play a prominent role. RING A BLUEY (5) stalked the lead but wound up strongly to score (22.71) at this track in Mix 6/7 FIN over 400m. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Has definite claims. MIGHTY HEIGHTY (8) will need to repeat last run to feature.",
